.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/README.md:16:`plugin_bridges/` contains the Node `.mjs` subprocess bridge between `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` and the standalone `mk_skill_advisor` MCP server.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/README.md:18:The bridge reads stdin JSON (prompt, workspaceRoot, thresholdConfidence), probes the advisor daemon, calls `advisor_recommend`, renders a brief and emits a single stdout JSON envelope (`{ status, brief, metadata }`). It fails open on all errors so the OpenCode plugin never blocks on advisor unavailability.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/README.md:20:This bridge was moved from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/` (pre-extraction legacy) to proper advisor ownership per ADR-003.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/README.md:28:| `mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs` | Stdin-to-stdout bridge: parses input, probes advisor, calls recommend, renders brief, emits JSON. |
