.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:3:description: "Bootstrap, verification, runtime hooks, compatibility shim, rollback, operator notes and reference commands for the native advisor_recommend architecture (merged INSTALL_GUIDE + SET-UP_GUIDE)."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:10:This is the canonical install + setup guide for the standalone Skill Advisor MCP server. The advisor runs as `mk_skill_advisor`, separate from `mk-spec-memory`. It preserves the public tool ids `advisor_recommend`, `advisor_rebuild`, `advisor_status`, `advisor_validate`, `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status`, `skill_graph_validate` plus one internal trusted-caller tool `skill_graph_propagate_enhances`. This document merges the previously-separate `SET-UP_GUIDE.md` (runtime hooks, rollback CLI, operator states, reference commands) into the install bootstrap so there is a single source of truth.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:19:I want to install the Skill Advisor MCP server (mk_skill_advisor) from .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:23:2. Install dependencies and build the advisor MCP server
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:25:4. Register or refresh the mk_skill_advisor server in my runtime (I'm using: [OpenCode / Claude Code / Codex / Gemini])
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:26:5. Verify advisor_status and advisor_recommend respond
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:33:- Install and build the standalone advisor MCP server
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:35:- Configure `mk_skill_advisor` for your runtime
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:36:- Confirm the 8 public advisor tools register and respond
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:44:The native advisor is a TypeScript package under `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/`. It exposes 8 public MCP tools (`advisor_recommend`, `advisor_rebuild`, `advisor_status`, `advisor_validate`, `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status`, `skill_graph_validate`) plus 1 internal trusted-caller tool (`skill_graph_propagate_enhances`, gated behind auth). The standalone MCP server owns the advisor handlers, schemas, launcher, plus the package-local SQLite DB at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite`. The Python `skill_advisor.py` shim remains as the compatibility surface for scripts and prompt hooks.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:50:- Node.js and npm available for the standalone system-skill-advisor MCP server.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:52:- Runtime MCP configuration includes both `mk-spec-memory` and `mk_skill_advisor`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:60:Install dependencies and build the advisor MCP server:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:63:npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server install
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:64:npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run build
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:70:test -e .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/node_modules/@spec-kit/shared && echo "shared dependency linked"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:73:Start or refresh the `mk_skill_advisor` MCP server in the active runtime. The launcher is:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:76:node .opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:83:Verify native tool registration through `mk_skill_advisor`:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:86:mk_skill_advisor.advisor_status({"workspaceRoot":"/absolute/path/to/repo"})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:87:mk_skill_advisor.advisor_recommend({"prompt":"save this conversation context to memory","options":{"topK":1}})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:88:mk_skill_advisor.advisor_validate({"skillSlug":null})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:91:Also verify the active runtime lists both MCP servers: `mk-spec-memory` for memory/context tools and `mk_skill_advisor` for advisor tools.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:95:- `advisor_status` returns `freshness`, `generation`, `trustState`, `lastGenerationBump`, `lastScanAt`, `skillCount` and `laneWeights`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:96:- `advisor_recommend` returns prompt-safe `recommendations[]`, cache state, lifecycle redirect metadata and freshness trust.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:97:- `advisor_rebuild` rebuilds stale, absent or unavailable advisor state and returns before/after freshness diagnostics.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:98:- `advisor_validate` returns real corpus, holdout, parity, safety and latency measurements.
