.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:298:The skill-advisor `semantic_shadow` lane runs against a pluggable embedder layer. As of phase `003/006` the contract surface (adapter interface, types, manifest registry, Ollama adapter) lives in `@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/` and is shared with `mk-spec-memory`. Skill-advisor's local `mcp_server/lib/embedders/` files are thin re-export shims plus a skill-advisor-specific `schema.ts` integration that targets the package-local SQLite database at `mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite`. This section is the new-user onboarding view; the canonical multi-MCP narrative lives at [embedder_pluggability.md](../system-spec-kit/references/memory/embedder_pluggability.md).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:313:Phase `002/jina-swap-and-reindex` runbook plus phase `004/skill-graph-db-writer-cross-wire` together make the swap safe end-to-end. The writer dispatcher (`refreshSkillEmbeddings()`) routes through `refreshSkillEmbeddingsViaAdapter` when an active pointer is set and falls back to the legacy `createEmbeddingsProvider` factory only when the cascade has not yet resolved (e.g. cold start before any probe succeeds).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:317:Source of truth: [`@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/registry.ts`](../system-spec-kit/shared/embeddings/registry.ts). Skill-advisor's local `mcp_server/lib/embedders/registry.ts` is a re-export shim — adding manifests is a single edit in the shared package. The seven text-tuned manifests registered today, each as a frozen `EmbedderManifest`:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:324:| `bge-large-en-v1.5` | 1024 | `ollama` | `bge-large-en-v1.5:latest` | n/a | BAAI flagship retrieval model. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:329:> **Content-type split.** The TS shared registry is text-tuned by design. The `contentType: 'text' \| 'code'` parameter on the shared cascade preserves the conceptual split for any future TS code consumer. The previous skill-advisor-specific `jina-embeddings-v2-base-code` entry was removed because it was code-tuned and did not belong in a text-only registry.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:345:const db = new Database('.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite');
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:353:- `vec_1024` table created (if absent), schema `(skill_id, embedding BLOB, model_id, content_hash, updated_at)`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:357:The mk-spec-memory `embedder_set` / `embedder_status` MCP tools are intentionally NOT mirrored here. Skill-advisor's surface is one database helper plus the cascade-driven sentinel. Operator discipline owns any manual swap workflow; there is no async re-index orchestrator on the skill-advisor side.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:367:5. Smoke-test via the `advisor_recommend` MCP tool against three queries (`"memory save"`, `"code search"`, `"spec folder"`) and confirm top-3 picks are sane.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:373:Skill-advisor does not ship an explicit `_resolve_device()` shim. Device selection inherits from the underlying backend:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:381:If you need MPS-style auto-detect for a local model, the Ollama backend already provides it on Apple Silicon by default — install Ollama, pull a manifest, the cascade picks it.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:385:- Canonical shared-embedder narrative: [`embedder_pluggability.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/memory/embedder_pluggability.md) — covers `mk-spec-memory`, skill-advisor and shared design rationale.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:386:- Shared contract surface: [`@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/`](../system-spec-kit/shared/embeddings/) — the canonical adapter, types, registry and Ollama adapter.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:389:- Skill-advisor schema helpers: [`mcp_server/lib/embedders/schema.ts`](./mcp_server/lib/embedders/schema.ts).
