.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:3:description: "Human-facing guide for the standalone system-skill-advisor skill, its mk_skill_advisor MCP server, scorer lanes, runtime hooks across Claude / Codex / Gemini / Devin / OpenCode plus operator workflows."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:5:  - "system skill advisor readme"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:6:  - "skill advisor"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:7:  - "mk_skill_advisor"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:8:  - "advisor_recommend"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:10:  - "skill advisor hook"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:25:You use `system-skill-advisor` when a runtime needs to pick a skill for a non-trivial prompt. It scores the prompt against indexed skill metadata, hook signals plus graph-derived relations, then returns calibrated recommendations with attribution. The advisor runs as a standalone MCP server called `mk_skill_advisor` so you can install, tune or replace it without touching memory or code-graph systems.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:31:The advisor is the canonical Gate 2 routing surface. Call `advisor_recommend` to pick a skill for a prompt, `advisor_status` to inspect freshness and trust state, `advisor_rebuild` to refresh the index after metadata changes, and `advisor_validate` for release and regression validation. Query the skill graph (depends_on, dependents, enhances, conflicts, hubs, subgraph) through `skill_graph_query`. For other concerns the advisor is not the right surface: structural code search belongs to a separate code-graph skill, semantic code search belongs to a semantic-index skill, and spec-folder memory belongs to a separate memory runtime.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:37:- **Daemon-backed freshness**. Watches `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` and `graph-metadata.json` and rebuilds advisor state on change.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:41:- **Python compatibility shim**. `skill_advisor.py` keeps scripts and hooks working when the native MCP path is not reachable.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:48:**Step 1: Check advisor health.**
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:53:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status({})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:61:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend({ "prompt": "create a new agent" })
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:69:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild({ "force": true })
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:72:Expected result: `rebuilt: true`, generation deltas, refreshed `skillCount`, plus diagnostics. Run only when `advisor_status` requires it or after touching skill metadata files.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:77:npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run typecheck
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:78:npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run build
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:89:The advisor is strongest when intent is ambiguous. It answers "which skill should handle this?" with calibrated confidence instead of guessing. It surfaces ambiguity explicitly when two top candidates are within striking distance of each other. Public responses are prompt-safe by design so you can log them in hook telemetry without leaking user prompt content.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:91:Routing is fail-open. When the native MCP path is unreachable the Python `skill_advisor.py` shim takes over and announces the degraded mode in its response. When freshness slips to `stale` or `absent` the advisor refuses to fabricate a recommendation and tells the caller what action to take.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:97:| `advisor_recommend` | Recommend skills for a prompt using the native scorer. | `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts`, `mcp_server/lib/scorer/` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:98:| `advisor_rebuild` | Rebuild the native advisor skill graph from checked-in metadata. | `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-rebuild.ts`, `mcp_server/lib/freshness/` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:99:| `advisor_status` | Report advisor freshness, trust state, lane weights plus daemon info. | `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-status.ts`, `mcp_server/lib/daemon/` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:100:| `advisor_validate` | Run the corpus, holdout, parity, safety plus latency check bundle. | `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-validate.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:109:| Lane | Live Weight | Role |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:124:| `stale` | Index is queryable but sources have changed. | Use with caveat, then call `advisor_rebuild`. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:125:| `absent` | Index is missing. | Call `advisor_rebuild`. Do not act on an empty result. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:135:system-skill-advisor/
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:156:    +-- advisor-server.ts             # Standalone mk_skill_advisor MCP entrypoint
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:177:| [references/scoring/advisor_scorer.md](./references/scoring/advisor_scorer.md) | Lane attribution model and fusion rules. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:178:| [references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md](./references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md) | Runtime hook contract for Claude, Codex, Gemini, Devin, OpenCode. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:186:| `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR` | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/` | Override the SQLite database directory. Must stay inside the workspace. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:190:| `SPECKIT_ADVISOR_SHADOW_MODE` | `0` | Set to `1` to disable the live scorer and run shadow-mode only. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:194:Per-call options on `advisor_recommend` (`topK`, `includeAttribution`) override matching defaults. Use environment variables for process-wide defaults and per-call options for one request.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:196:`mk_skill_advisor` participates in the shared native MCP lifecycle guardrails. The server refreshes idle activity from primary stdio and secondary IPC socket connect/data/write events. Orphan cleanup and LaunchAgent rollout are documented centrally in the [repo scripts runbook](../../scripts/README.md); the LaunchAgent remains a template until explicitly installed by an operator.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:200:The `semantic_shadow` lane (lowest live weight at `0.05`) runs against a pluggable embedder layer shared with `mk-spec-memory`. The contract lives in `@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/`: an `EmbedderAdapter` interface, a frozen `MANIFESTS` registry of seven text-tuned candidates (`nomic-embed-text-v1.5`, `mxbai-embed-large-v1`, `bge-small-en-v1.5`, `bge-large-en-v1.5`, `jina-embeddings-v3`, `bge-m3`, `snowflake-arctic-embed-l-v2.0`) and a `setActiveEmbedder(db, name, dim)` helper that writes the active pointer into the package-local `skill-graph.sqlite`. Skill-advisor's local `mcp_server/lib/embedders/` files are thin re-export shims. (Note: skill-advisor's `setActiveEmbedder` is 3-arg; mk-spec-memory ships a 4-arg variant that also persists the cascade-tier provider in `vec_metadata`. The two helpers diverge by design — skill-advisor recovers provider from the manifest backend at need. See [embedder_pluggability.md](../system-spec-kit/references/memory/embedder_pluggability.md) for the cross-skill comparison.)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:206:See [INSTALL_GUIDE.md §12 "Choosing an embedder"](./INSTALL_GUIDE.md#12--choosing-an-embedder) for the cascade tier table, swap workflow, and content-type rationale. See [`embedder_pluggability.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/memory/embedder_pluggability.md) for the canonical shared-embedder narrative covering mk-spec-memory alongside skill-advisor.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:216:Tool path: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:225:Tool path: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:234:Tool path: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:243:Tool path: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_propagate_enhances
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:244:Arguments: { "mode": "report", "minConfidence": 0.6 }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:254:| `trustState: "stale"` | Source skill metadata changed since the last index build. | Call `advisor_rebuild` with `force: true`. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:255:| `trustState: "absent"` | The advisor SQLite database is missing or empty. | Call `advisor_rebuild`. If that fails, check `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR` and disk permissions. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:256:| `trustState: "unavailable"` | Native MCP path cannot be reached. | Verify `mk_skill_advisor` is registered in `opencode.json`. Fall back to `scripts/skill_advisor.py` if needed. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:258:| `advisor_validate` baseline drift (corpus top-1 below 80.5%) | Scorer behavior changed or fixtures drifted. | Inspect `perSkill[]` and `slices.corpus` to identify regressed skills. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:259:| Recommendations omit a newly-added skill | The advisor reads metadata at every call, but the daemon may not have observed the new file yet. | Call `advisor_rebuild` or wait for the watcher to fire. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:266:**Q: Why is the advisor a separate MCP server instead of part of `mk-spec-memory`?**
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:268:A: Routing is operationally distinct from memory. You may want to roll back, restart, tune the advisor without touching memory state. The standalone server boundary makes that safe.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:272:A: Yes, but the change must come with measured evidence. The advisor exposes `advisor_validate` for corpus, holdout, parity, safety plus latency slices. Run a baseline, change weights in `lib/scorer/lane-registry.ts`, re-run validate, then ship the diff with the doc updates in `references/scoring/advisor_scorer.md` and `feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:274:**Q: How does the advisor stay safe to call from hooks?**
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:280:A: Memory, spec folders, continuity stay in `system-spec-kit`. The advisor depends on `system-spec-kit` only for the heavyweight embeddings stack used by the optional `semantic_shadow` lane. Non-embeddings code is fully isolated as of v0.2.0.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:284:A: See [references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md](./references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md) for the advisor hook contract across Claude, Codex, Gemini, Devin plus the OpenCode plugin.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md:296:| [references/scoring/advisor_scorer.md](./references/scoring/advisor_scorer.md) | Lane attribution model and fusion rules. |
