.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:18:`lib/cross-skill-edges/` detects missing inbound `enhances` edges from skill metadata and can apply selected high-confidence candidates back to `graph-metadata.json`. Report mode is the default; write mode must stay explicit.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:26:| Candidate detection | Skill advisor | Uses metadata signals to infer inbound edge candidates. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:27:| Graph metadata writes | Source skill package | Apply mode writes only selected candidates back to source metadata. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:47:- Default to report/propose mode for diagnostics.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:48:- Keep apply mode explicit, scoped and path-boundary checked.
