.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tools/README.md:18:`mcp_server/tools/` contains MCP `ToolDefinition` descriptors for the standalone `mk_skill_advisor` surface. Each descriptor defines a tool name, prompt-safe description and JSON Schema input contract.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tools/README.md:22:- `advisor_recommend` routes prompts through the native advisor scorer.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tools/README.md:23:- `advisor_status` reports freshness, trust state and daemon availability.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tools/README.md:24:- `advisor_rebuild` rebuilds checked-in skill metadata when status is stale or absent.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tools/README.md:25:- `advisor_validate` runs the heavier advisor validation bundle after explicit confirmation.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tools/README.md:26:- `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status` and `skill_graph_validate` expose the advisor-owned skill graph MCP surface.
