.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:2:title: "Architecture: system-skill-advisor"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:3:description: "Current package architecture for system-skill-advisor: scorer, daemon, MCP runtime, skill graph, hook integration, and validators."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:5:  - "system skill advisor architecture"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:6:  - "skill advisor architecture"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:7:  - "advisor scorer"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:8:  - "advisor daemon"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:13:# Architecture: system-skill-advisor
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:15:> Current-reality architecture for the `system-skill-advisor` package. The advisor scores prompts against indexed skill metadata, exposes recommendations through a standalone MCP server, and rebuilds state through a file watcher.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:21:`system-skill-advisor` is the standalone routing runtime that picks the right skill for a non-trivial prompt. It runs as its own MCP server (`mk_skill_advisor`) and persists state to a local SQLite skill graph.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:29:The recommendation surface is `advisor_recommend`. The trust surface is `advisor_status`. The refresh surface is `advisor_rebuild`. The skill-graph query surface is `skill_graph_query`. Detail per tool lives in `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:59:│  │ skill_advisor  │────▶│ skill-graph     │                     │
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:76:system-skill-advisor/
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:109:The advisor treats its SQLite skill graph as the durable record. Recommendations are read-only over that record; the daemon refreshes it from authored skill metadata.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:111:**Read path (`advisor_recommend`):** input prompt enters `handlers/recommend.ts`, the scorer fuses 5 lanes, the result joins with trust-state metadata, and the handler returns a calibrated `recommendations[]` array with prompt-safe attribution.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:113:**Write path (`advisor_rebuild`):** the rebuilder scans `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` and `graph-metadata.json`, applies the affordance normalizer, persists rows to the skill graph, and bumps the generation counter. Daemon watches the same paths and triggers incremental rebuilds on file change.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:133:**Compatibility shim.** `compat/skill_advisor.py` keeps scripts and hooks working when the native MCP path is not reachable. The shim wraps the same recommendation logic with a Python entrypoint.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:139:The advisor ships matching prompt-submit hooks for Claude Code, Codex, Gemini, and Devin CLI, plus an OpenCode plugin bridge. The hook payload is the same compact attribution-safe JSON across runtimes so callers can rely on consistent fields regardless of transport. The plugin bridge under `.opencode/plugins/` calls into `mcp_server/lib/hooks/` and emits the payload back to the runtime.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:147:**Release validation.** `advisor_validate` runs the regression suite and reports threshold semantics (aggregate vs runtime) plus a prompt-safe `telemetry.outcomes.totals` block. Hook diagnostics persist to bounded JSONL sinks so `advisor_validate` can read them back across processes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/05-trust-state.md:17:Give every consumer (native MCP tools, CLI hooks, plugin bridge, Python shim) a single shared vocabulary for describing whether advisor state is current, aged, missing or unreadable, without ever blocking the reader.
