.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:4:**Source directive**: user, "all 3 system skills need to be completely isolated. Users can delete system-spec-kit and expect a functioning system-code-graph and skill-advisor"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:6:**Versioning note**: pre-1.0 preview track. v0.2.0 reflects the substantive nature of the isolation work. Runtime API ids (`advisor_recommend`, `advisor_rebuild`, `advisor_status`, `advisor_validate`, `skill_graph_*`) remain stable from v0.1.0.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:12:system-skill-advisor was hard-coupled to system-spec-kit at the import level, 6 production .ts files imported cross-skill helpers (shared-payload types + unicode-normalization). v0.2.0 closes all 6 by duplicating the small types locally into `mcp_server/lib/shared/` and routing the heavyweight embeddings stack through a visible symlink (user's chosen pattern: "make the dependency visible to repo users").
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:17:skill-advisor tsc exit BEFORE removing system-spec-kit:  1 (TS5101 baseUrl warning)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:18:skill-advisor tsc exit AFTER removing system-spec-kit:   2 (NEW errors, symlinked embeddings dangled)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:19:skill-advisor tsc exit AFTER restoring system-spec-kit:  1 (back to baseline)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:22:Interpretation: skill-advisor's NON-embeddings code is fully isolated. Embeddings-touching files (semantic-shadow lane + skill-graph-db's embedding load) fail when system-spec-kit is removed, by design, via a dangling symlink that telegraphs the missing dependency.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:26:#### Local lib/shared/ created with 7 types + canonicalFold
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:28:- Need: 4 production .ts files imported `AdvisorEnvelopeMetadata`, `AdvisorEnvelopeFreshness`, `AdvisorEnvelopeStatus`, `SharedPayloadEnvelope`, `SharedPayloadSection`, `SharedPayloadSourceRef`, `SharedPayloadTrustState` from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/context/shared-payload.ts`. Two of them imported `canonicalFold` from `system-spec-kit/shared/unicode-normalization.ts`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:29:- Change: new `mcp_server/lib/shared/shared-payload.ts` carries 7 types + transitive helpers (~1099 lines). New `mcp_server/lib/shared/unicode-normalization.ts` carries the full `canonicalFold` function + `CANONICAL_FOLD_VERSION` + `HIDDEN_CHAR_PATTERN` + `COMBINING_MARK_PATTERN` + `CONFUSABLE_REPLACEMENTS` (74 lines).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:37:- Change: `mcp_server/lib/shared/embeddings` is now a symlink to `../../../../system-spec-kit/shared/embeddings`. The symlink is visible in the file tree, repo users can see "this skill depends on system-spec-kit/shared/embeddings". Consumers import via the `@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/factory.js` workspace alias (resolved by tsconfig paths to the real location, bypassing the symlink-resolution edge cases). Both consumer files carry NOTE comments explaining the symlink contract.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:44:- Need: `mcp_server/package.json` declared `"@spec-kit/shared": "file:../../system-spec-kit/shared"` as a workspace dep. That declaration was the runtime "magic" that made the alias resolve via `npm install`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:45:- Change: declaration removed (and `package-lock.json` regenerated). The `@spec-kit/shared` workspace alias now resolves ONLY via tsconfig paths, type-check-only. Runtime imports resolve via the file system (through the symlink).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:52:- Need: `tests/handlers/advisor-recommend.vitest.ts` imported `buildErrorResponse`, `ErrorCodes`, `MemoryError` from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/errors.ts`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:54:- Why it matters: test suite is now cross-skill-import-free. Vitest discovers 24 advisor tests post-refactor.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:58:#### CI guardrail covers skill-advisor
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:60:- Need: the existing CI workflow had no reverse-direction audit for skill-advisor (only for code-graph).
