.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:100:- The symlink at `lib/shared/embeddings` is git-tracked and will recreate on checkout (git stores it via mode 120000).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:107:- **`tsconfig.json` extends from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tsconfig.json`**, at the build-config level, skill-advisor still references system-spec-kit. Deleting system-spec-kit breaks `tsc --build` via the inherited config. Inlining the base config is a future cleanup if pursued.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:108:- **tsc emits `TS6307 File is in the program because ...` informational notes** for files reached through the `@spec-kit/shared/embeddings/*` alias, these are NOT errors (exit code 0). They describe the cross-skill program structure, which is the architectural truth.
