.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:1:This release lands the system-skill-advisor portion of the packets 108 plus 110 auto-review uplift program. Four reusable teachings from the upstream `dzianisv/opencode-plugins` auto-review package now apply to both the skill internals and the `mk-skill-advisor.js` plugin: async file I/O with a closure-scoped lazy-mkdir guard, opt-in debug logging, a 4-tier configuration precedence and awaited config loading at module init. Every mechanism cleared a 5-of-5 unanimous deep-ai-council review by `cli-codex gpt-5.5 xhigh fast` before any code shipped and the council reshaped the H-3 plus H-6 scope in a load-bearing way: the disk writes had to remain AWAITED rather than fire-and-forget so the bounded-retention contract for metrics records survives.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:11:The advisor's metrics persistence in `mcp_server/lib/metrics.ts` used synchronous `mkdirSync` plus `writeFileSync` to flush diagnostic and outcome records, which blocked the event loop on every advisor invocation. The hot path is now `await mkdir` plus `await writeFile` from `fs/promises`, gated by a closure-scoped `dirReady = false` flag that ensures the directory check runs exactly once per process. The two persistence entrypoints (`persistAdvisorHookDiagnosticRecord` and `persistAdvisorHookOutcomeRecord`) are now async functions that await the underlying writes. Bounded-retention semantics, read the file, slice the last N records, rewrite the file, are preserved per the council's section 10.1 mandate, because making the writes fire-and-forget would have allowed unbounded growth between rotations.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:21:#### 4-tier configuration precedence in `mk-skill-advisor.js`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:23:The plugin used to read configuration only from `rawOptions` passed at construction. Operators who wanted to override advisor behavior outside of the OpenCode config had no surface to do so. The plugin now loads configuration through `loadConfig()` with a 4-tier precedence: `rawOptions` wins first, then a JSON config file at `~/.config/opencode/plugin/mk-skill-advisor.json`, then 7 new `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_*` environment-variable fallbacks, then hardcoded defaults. The legacy `SPEC_KIT_PLUGIN_NODE_BINARY` env-var is preserved as a backward-compat fallback for the node-binary path. The existing env-var disable handling at lines 35 through 39 of the plugin is left untouched so operators who only ever used the disable switch see no behavior change.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:46:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/metrics.ts` | Lines 218 through 248 (per the council-revised contract): `mkdirSync` plus `writeFileSync` replaced with awaited `mkdir` plus `writeFile` from `fs/promises`. Closure-scoped `dirReady` flag introduced at module scope (line 154); `SKILL_ADVISOR_DEBUG=1` enable gate added for diagnostic records. Bounded-retention read-then-rewrite-last-N preserved at line 253. `persistAdvisorHookDiagnosticRecord` and `persistAdvisorHookOutcomeRecord` now async. Touched in 65e6f0479. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:47:| `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` | New `loadConfig()` reading `~/.config/opencode/plugin/mk-skill-advisor.json`; 4-tier precedence (rawOptions > file > env > defaults); 7 new `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_*` env-var fallbacks; `SPEC_KIT_PLUGIN_NODE_BINARY` preserved as backward-compat fallback; `configPromise` loaded at module init. Factory awaits `configPromise` before option normalization. Existing env-var disable handling at lines 35 through 39 preserved unchanged. Touched in 45c5a7118. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:67:No migration required. Pick up the new release and the plugin will discover any pre-existing `~/.config/opencode/plugin/mk-skill-advisor.json` on first invocation. Set `SKILL_ADVISOR_DEBUG=1` if you want diagnostic records persisted. Leave it unset for the quiet default.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/bench/latency-bench.ts:28:  console.log(`advisor-promotion-latency-bench ${JSON.stringify(report)}`);
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/07--hooks-and-plugin/04-codex-hook.md:3:description: "Codex CLI adapters using native SessionStart startup context and UserPromptSubmit advisor brief injection, with a prompt-wrapper fallback for older deployments."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/07--hooks-and-plugin/04-codex-hook.md:8:  - "codex advisor hook"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/07--hooks-and-plugin/04-codex-hook.md:17:Support Codex CLI sessions with native startup-context and prompt-time advisor injection when `[features].codex_hooks = true` is enabled. Older deployments, missing hook configs or restricted hosts can still use the prompt-wrapper fallback for the advisor path.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/07--hooks-and-plugin/04-codex-hook.md:21:`hooks/codex/session-start.ts` handles native `SessionStart` startup, resume and clear events and returns `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext`. `hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.ts` handles native `UserPromptSubmit` advisor briefs. User-level `~/.codex/hooks.json` registers the compiled `SessionStart` and `UserPromptSubmit` entries alongside Superset `notify.sh` and `~/.codex/config.toml` must enable `codex_hooks = true`. `hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.ts` remains the fallback prompt-wrapper path for Codex deployments that do not expose the hook surface. `.codex/policy.json` ships the Bash denylist. The native prompt hook and wrapper share failure semantics and the global disable flag.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/01-watcher.md:17:Keep the advisor graph fresh without incurring the cost of watching the whole workspace. The narrow-scope watcher subscribes only to files that can affect routing: each skill's `SKILL.md`, its `graph-metadata.json` and any path declared under `derived.key_files`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/01-watcher.md:29:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/daemon/watcher.ts` | Daemon | Source reference |
