.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/README.md:5:  - "skill advisor database"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/README.md:19:The default database path is `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite`. SQLite sidecars such as `-wal` and `-shm`, launcher lease files and duplicate generated JSON fallbacks live beside it when the database is active, but they are ignored runtime state.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/README.md:23:Runtime state belongs to the standalone advisor package. Tests may override the directory with `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR`; `SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR` remains a legacy fallback. Operator documentation should treat the package-local path as canonical.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/README.md:33:| `.mk-skill-advisor-launcher.json` | Ignored launcher lease state. |
