.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/06-rebuild-from-source.md:3:description: "Recovery path that reconstructs the advisor graph from SKILL.md and graph-metadata.json sources when the SQLite database is corrupt or unreadable."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/06-rebuild-from-source.md:8:  - "advisor recovery"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/06-rebuild-from-source.md:17:Ensure the advisor never gets stuck in an unrecoverable state when SQLite storage is corrupted. The rebuild-from-source path reconstructs routable state from the authoritative source files without user intervention.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/06-rebuild-from-source.md:21:`lib/freshness/rebuild-from-source.ts` detects a corrupt or unreadable SQLite store via the daemon lifecycle, then walks `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` plus each `graph-metadata.json`, applies the auto-indexing derivation pipeline and republishes a fresh snapshot. Throughout the rebuild, readers see `unavailable` trust state and fail-open responses rather than exceptions. Rebuild is also the canonical recovery path for the H5 operator playbook.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/06-rebuild-from-source.md:29:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/freshness/rebuild-from-source.ts` | Library | Source reference |
