.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:3:description: "Lane B scripts that dispatch a model under test and score its fixture outputs by pattern or 5-dimension scoring."
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:16:`model-benchmark/` owns the Lane B (model-benchmark) executables: dispatch a model or prompt framework against benchmark fixtures, then score the materialized outputs. It pairs a CLI dispatcher with a fixture scorer and delegates 5-dimension scoring to the `scorer/` subtree.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:20:- `dispatch-model.cjs` routes a prompt to one of five executors and returns the model output as a JSON envelope plus raw stdout and stderr.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:21:- `run-benchmark.cjs` reads a benchmark profile, scores each fixture output, and writes `report.json` plus a label-stamped history snapshot.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:22:- Two scoring methods exist: `pattern` (default heading/pattern matcher) and `5dim` (opt-in, routed through `scorer/`).
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:23:- `loop-host.cjs` in `../shared/` is the router. It resolves the bare names `run-benchmark.cjs` and `dispatch-model.cjs` to this folder at spawn time.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/README.md:35:│ loop-host.cjs    │ ───▶ │ dispatch-model.cjs  │ ───▶ │ executor CLI     │
